  "text": "In humans there is also evidence for a set of common alleles occurring at elevated frequencies and across populations [CITATION_1] . This is comparable to the set of shared alleles that we find in mice, most of which occur also across subspecies. This suggests that they have a specific adaptive value, which maintains them or allows them to introgress between the diverse lineages. On the other hand, the rare alleles occur only locally, both in humans [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and mice (this study).",
